commit.message:
Add `typeobj` to `dtype`

Allows users to get the underlying `typeobj` (e.g. `numpy.float64`) from
the `dtype`.

Add NPY_CASTING

Include `NPY_CASTING` along with the other things `extern`ed from
`numpy/arrayobject.h`.
Try to fix travis installation of gcc-8 on xenial.

Fix calling va_arg function with a NULL argument from generated C++ code

C++ allows NULL to be a literal 0 [1], and this actually happens on some Linux
systems when linux/stddef.h happens to be included [2]. When 0 is passed to a
variadic function as a 7th or later argument, it is passed on the stack, and
Clang encodes this on AMD64 with "mov dword ptr [rsp], 0" because it is an
int. This sets lower 32 bits to zero, but leaves upper 32 bits unchanged.
When they happen to be non zero, the called function that expects the last
argument to be a zero pointer reads past the last intended argument and
eventually segfaults.

[1] https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/types/NULL
[2] https://stackoverflow.com/a/31285400/1687334
[3] https://godbolt.org/g/o4Av7Q

commit.message: Fix constant folding test in Py2.

Add Python Raw memory helper functions

In Python 3.4+, Raw memory helper functions were added to wrap, track,
and check `malloc` and `free` calls for C memory outside of the GIL.
These have the same API as the existing `PyMem_*` calls except they use
Raw and never require the GIL. For Python 2/3 compatibility, export the
existing `PyMem_` functions on Python 2 as `PyMem_Raw` where they act
basically equivalently. These are especially important as Python 3.6
changed the existing `PyMem_` functions to allocate from pymalloc
instead of the C allocator meaning the GIL must now be held with them.
So these are Python 2/3 alternatives that can be relied on to not
require the GIL.

Define Python Raw Mem helpers in ModuleSetupCode

To handle the Python version differences, handle the definitions of
`PyMem_Raw*` functions in `ModuleSetupCode`. Then extern them in
`cpython.mem` without using a version check or a specific header.
Define Raw memory functions near non-Raw ones

Tweak Raw memory macros' version constraint

Technically these functions were around in some of the Python 3.4
prereleases. So add a more accurate version constraint.

commit.message: Support test skipping also in run tests.
Fix test runner in Py2.6.
Fix sharded testing in travis.
Try to fix a test under MacOS.
Fix another Py2.6 test runner problem.
Use "travis_retry" script to see if it improves the build reliability.
Mark the "with_statement" __future__ feature as no-op since it's always on.
Avoid depending on some C macros in the buildenv.pyx test that might not be defined (specifically on MSVC, as usual).
Add links to our CI servers to the docs on contributing.
Minor simplification in debug code.
Try to reduce test log clutter in MSVC output.
Reduce number of test shards on appveyor to see if that speeds up the overall test time.
Write regular time stamps into the test log to spot slow running tests.
Remove docs note about fused types being "experimental". They are old enough by now to consider them an established language feature.
Allow explicit "-2" option for the cythonize script to set the language level to 2 (the current, but not future, default).
Mark try-finally statements with terminating finally clauses as terminators themselves.
Print total test time when multiple shards are used.
Increase number of test shards again as 4 instead of 7 made it a bit slower. So let's try 5.
Direct all test output in the test runner to stderr because that's where unittest is writing it, and it gives better ordering on Windows to not mix stdout and stderr.
Ignore test time-stamper thread when checking for thread termination.
Extend module reimport test to also try reimports without knowing the package.
Fix daemon thread setup in test runner for Py2.6.
Implement safe-guard to prevent loading Cython modules into multiple subinterpreters.
Add declarations from CPython's "pylifecycle.h".
Add C-API function declaration for PyInterpreterState_GetID(), which is new on Py3.7.
Minor C-API declaration fix.
Update changelog.
Extend CPython C-API test to at least include (and thus parser) all .pxd files.
Add warning to PyThreadState_Swap() that it should not be used in Cython code because Cython makes the assumption that the current thread state does not change in arbitrary places.
Raise a more appropriate ImportError rather than a generic RuntimeError when trying to re-import a Cython module in a different subinterpreter with PEP-489.
Add test for Cython module usage in subinterpreters. In Py3.5, we should now raise an exception when trying to re-import a module into a different subinterpreter.
Clarify import error message: subinterpreters are supported, just not more than one.
Fix test command line to make it work on Windows.
Add a "CYTHON_HEX_VERSION" macro in the style of PY_HEX_VERSION that user code can use to detect the Cython version that generated the main module.
Update changelog.
Print run time stats in the test runner.
Fix some stats issues in the test runner.
Avoid printing test stats when no tests have run.
Improve test stats formatting.
Enable coverage reporting in travis runs. Merge C/C++ jobs into one to simplify that (we have enough jobs to keep travis busy).
Restrict PyPy tests to C again (we always excluded C++ for time reasons).
Fix typos in travis script.
Reorder and clean up travis build config to make the most interesting jobs run first: Py2.7/3.7/2.6.
Show ccache stats in travis after test runs.
Added the pep8 rule: W291 trailing whitespaces.
Show slowest N tests in test stats per metric.
